#. Tag: title
#: backup.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring backups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Before you can start to back up data, configure which files to back up, which ones to ignore and where to store the backup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure which folders to back up by clicking <guimenu>Folders to save</guimenu> . By default, your home directory is preconfigured. Use the plus and minus signs to add or delete folders."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optionally, configure folders that should be ignored when backing up data by clicking <guimenu>Folders to ignore</guimenu> . By default, the trash bin and the <filename>Download</filename> directory are preconfigured. Use the plus and minus signs to add or delete folders."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "To define a location where to store the backup, click <guimenu>Storage location</guimenu> . You can choose a <guimenu>Local Folder</guimenu> , a <guimenu>Network Server</guimenu> , or cloud storage. If you opt for the latter, make sure you have provided your login credentials for the respective online service via <guimenu>Open Online Account Settings</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "Regardless of the Storage location, provide a directory name under which the backup(s) will be stored. It is recommended to choose a name that can easily be associated with backups for the respective machine and data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: backup.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating backups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Once you have configured which folders to back up and where to store them, you have two choices for backing up. First, by manually starting the backup. Switch to the <guimenu>Overview</guimenu> screen and click <guimenu>Back Up Now</guimenu> . Choose whether you want to protect the backup with a password or not. Proceed with <guimenu>Forward</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "The second option is to schedule automatic backups: Create a backup schedule by clicking <guimenu>Scheduling</guimenu> . Enter the backup frequency and decide how long to keep backups. Enable scheduled backups by turning the <guimenu>Automatic Backup</guimenu> switch <guimenu>On</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: backup.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restoring data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "To restore a previous state of your data, switch to the <guimenu>Overview</guimenu> screen and click <guimenu>Restore</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose a backup location, a directory name and proceed with <guimenu>Forward</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the backup date which you want to restore and proceed with <guimenu>Forward</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose whether to restore the files from the backup to their original location or to a different directory. Proceed with <guimenu>Forward</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: backup.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Review your settings. If necessary, go <guimenu>Back</guimenu> to change them. To start restoring data from the backup, click <guimenu>Restore</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

